rooms.Name: The castle gates.
rooms.Description:
The gates to the once proud palace, are now rusting, and falling off thier
hinges. Inside the gates is the riuns of a royal palace. Some of the marble
walls still stand, and alow you to make out what the castle must have looked
like in its prime.

rooms.Name: Inside the gates of the palace.
rooms.Description:
You stand inside what was once a long hallway. Now the roof has fallen in,
and the walls have crumbled to the ground. The floor is overrun with cracks,
and large patches of grass, and other weeds infest the passage.

rooms.Name: The courtyard.
rooms.Description:
As you walk into this open space you realize that it was once the public
courtyard of the palace. In the center is the remains of a statue, now
shatered and in ruins. However a plaque at the base of the statue still
remains, and appears readable.

ExtraDescs.Description:
The plaque at the base of the statue reads:

I am Ozymandias, greatest of all kings.
Look on my works ye mighty, and dispair!

rooms.Name: The audience hall.
rooms.Description:
This was once the mighty audience chamber of the great King Ozymandias.
The decrepit stone throne lays crumbling at one end of the recatngular hall
. Before the throne are two long rectangular sone pits. At the bottom of the
pitts are long jagged spikes.

rooms.Name: A small alcove.
rooms.Description:
This room is still mostly intact. The walls, and most of the ceiling are still
in decent shape, and for the most part still standing. On the floor is a
wooden trap door. It was once locked, but the lock has rusted off.

rooms.Name: The crypt.
rooms.Description:
This is a dank underground room used for burrying the dead. The walls are
line with stone caskets. Most of them are decorated with jems, and gold.
The remains of the deceased are mumified, and decorated with fine cloths,
and jewelry.

rooms.Name: A secret room.
rooms.Description:
This dark unlit chamber was hidden from people to stash more valuable treasuers.
The walls, and floor are made of neatly carved stone. There are spiderwebs in
the corners, and on the ceilings.

rooms.Name: A hallway in the dungeon.
rooms.Description:
This is where prisoners are tortured, and kill. The walls are lined with chains
and shackles user to chain prisoners to the wall. Several partial human corpses,
and skeletons line the walls of the room.

rooms.Name: Standing before the wizards tower.
rooms.Description:
Towering before you is the sanctuary of the wizard of the palace. Surprisingly
it is the only structure left standing. It appears to be immune to the wear and
tear of time. There is a glowing door at the base of the tower leading north.

rooms.Name: A large round room.
rooms.Description:

continues on. To the west is a stone door. A large iron padlock ensures that
it is not opened.

north. The door is made of stone, yet has a faint red glow. You can feel a
powerfull heat emenating from the door.

rooms.Name: A stone passage.

this there is an oaken door to the south. Strange hissing noises come from
the other side of the door.

rooms.Name: A cold passage.
rooms.Description:
The walls of the passage are covered with frost. The air is cold, and a rushing
noise comes from underneath the door to the west. The crack between the door
and the floor is covered by a sheet of ice.

rooms.Name: The first floor of the tower.
rooms.Description:
The inside of the tower is as well preserved as the outside. The walls are
lined with intricate tapestries. The is a spiral staircase lead up the entire
length of the tower.
